CONFIGURING/CREATING GUNICORN SERVICE:
1- run "sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/gunicorn.service" : and paste this file

[Unit]
Description=gunicorn daemon
After=network.target

[Service]
User=ubuntu
Group=www-data
WorkingDirectory=/home/ubuntu/hms-project/hms
ExecStart=/home/ubuntu/venv/bin/gunicorn \
          --workers 3 \
          --bind unix:/home/ubuntu/hms-project/hms/gunicorn.sock \
          config.wsgi:application



2 - run "sudo systemctl daemon-reload" :This RELOAD SYSTEMD
3 - run "sudo systemctl start gunicorn" :This START GUNICORN
4 - run "sudo systemctl enable gunicorn" :This ENABLE GUNICORN and ensures your app starts automatically after reboot.
5 -run "sudo systemctl status gunicorn" : THIS CHECKS IF GUNICORN is running
6 -run "sudo journalctl -u gunicorn" or
  -run "sudo journalctl -u gunicorn --no-pager" : This is VERY IMPORTANT.
It shows:"syntax errors,missing,packages,bad paths,missing environment variables,migration problems


